The DA has accused Bell Pottinger of stirring racial tensions through some of the work it has done for the Gupta-owned Oakbay. JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) says it trusts the right decision will be made in its case against Bell Pottinger.Both parties appeared before the Public Relations and Communications Associations' (PRICA) disciplinary committee yesterday.The DA has accused the PR agency of stirring racial tensions through some of the work it has done for the Gupta-owned Oakbay.The PRCA is set to hand down its ruling in the next 2 weeks.The DA's Phumzile van Damme said, We have been represented a solid case, unfortunately, the hearing was private we now await the committee to tell us what their ruling is. 